subaward_description:
AGREE:    $21,561
AMEND1:   $26,573
AMEND2: 26,562

1) OVERVIEW 
.	I)  BACKGROUND. TO CHARACTERIZE DIFFERENTIATION OF HEMATOPOIETIC STEM AND PROGENITOR CELLS &#8232;UPON INTERFERON GAMMA STIMULATION, WE PROPOSE TO PERFORM STATISTICAL ANALYSES OF LINEAGE TRACING DATA (LABELING FREQUENCIES) AND HIGH-THROUGHPUT SEQUENCING DATA REVEALING BARCODE TAGS CARRIED IN HEMATOPOIETIC CELLS. &#8232;
.	II)  SCOPE. THIS PROPOSAL ENCOMPASSES A COLLABORATION TO USE LINEAGE TRACING AND BARCODING DATA TO UNDERSTAND THE CLONAL ORIGINS OF MYELOID BLOOD CELLS DURING INFLAMMATORY STRESS. &#8232;
.	III)  OBJECTIVES. OUR OBJECTIVES ARE TO 
.	(1)  MEASURE THE CONTRIBUTION OF PRIMITIVE PROGENITORS (I.E. HSCS VERSUS MPPS) TO &#8232;MYELOPOIESIS AFTER INTERFERON GAMMA (IFNG) STIMULATION USING LINEAGE TRACING. &#8232;
.	(2)  MEASURE THE CONTRIBUTION OF PRIMITIVE PROGENITORS (I.E. HSCS VERSUS MPPS) TO &#8232;MYELOPOIESIS AFTER INTERFERON GAMMA (IFNG) STIMULATION USING CELLULAR BARCODING. &#8232;
2) REQUIREMENTS 
.	I)  TASKS 
.	(1)  THE KIMMEL LAB WILL DEVELOP A MATHEMATICAL MODEL BASED ON DIFFERENTIAL EQUATIONS TO &#8232;DESCRIBE THE RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN THE POPULATION SIZE OF VARIOUS PROGENITOR POPULATIONS (HSC, MPP, MYELOID PROGENITOR, GRANULOCYTE), AND THEIR DIVISION RATE. THIS MODEL WILL BE BASED ON STEADY STATE DATA AND WILL BE USED TO MODEL ALTERATIONS IN SYSTEM DURING INFLAMMATORY STRESS. &#8232;
.	(2)  THE KING LAB WILL PROVIDE RAW DATA REGARDING THE NUMBER AND DIVISION RATE (BETA) OF HEMATOPOIETIC PROGENITORS DURING STRESS. FURTHER, THE KING LAB WILL PROVIDE DATA REGARDING LABELING FREQUENCY (F) OF AN HSC-SPECIFIC FLUORESCENT TAG IN DOWNSTREAM POPULATIONS AFTER IFNG STRESS. FINALLY, THE KING LAB WILL PROVIDE IDENTITY, NUMBER, AND FREQUENCY OF TRANSPOSON TAGS IDENTIFIED BY SEQUENCING IN POOLED SAMPLES OF HEMATOPOIETIC POPULATIONS. &#8232;
.	(3)  THE KIMMEL LAB WILL USE THE MATHEMATICAL MODEL TO CALCULATE THE DIFFERENTIATION RATE (ALPHA) OF A GIVEN POPULATION IN LIGHT OF KNOWN DIVISION RATE (BETA) AND LABELING FREQUENCY (F). THEY WILL ALSO PERFORM ANALYSIS TO DETERMINE STATISTICAL SIGNIFICANCE OF THE FINDINGS. &#8232;
.	II)  DELIVERABLES. THE KIMMEL LAB WILL PROVIDE MATHEMATICAL FORMULAS. FROM THE LINEAGE TRACING DATA, THE KIMMEL LAB WILL PROVIDE AN ESTIMATE OF THE CHANGE IN DIVISION (BETA) AND DIFFERENTIATION (ALPHA) RATES DURING IFNG STRESS AT THE HST-TO-MPP AND CMP-TO-GMP STAGES OF DIFFERENTIATION. FOR THE BARCODING DATA, THE KIMMEL LAB WILL PROVIDE A STATISTICAL ANALYSIS OF THE DIFFERENCE IN BARCODE OVERLAP BETWEEN THE HSC, MPP, AND GRANULOCYTE POPULATIONS AT STEADY STATE AND DURING IFNG STRESS. &#8232;
.	III)  SCHEDULE. EACH OBJECTIVE IS ANTICIPATED TO TAKE ~2 YEARS TO COMPLETE, ONCE EMPIRICAL DATA IS PROVIDED BY THE KING LAB. THE FINAL YEAR OF THE PROJECT IS RESERVED FOR MANUSCRIPT PREPARATION. &#8232;
.	IV)  ASSUMPTIONS. DATA RESULTING FROM THIS COLLABORATION WILL BE SHARED BETWEEN THE LABS AND PUBLISHED JOINTLY. &#8232;
3) GOVERNMENT FURNISHED PROPERTY. NONE.&#8232;4) SECURITY REQUIREMENTS. NO SPECIAL SECURITY REQUIREMENTS.

STATEMENT OF WORK FOR SEDIMENTOLOGISTS (MSP)
(REVISED 12/21)
CORE DESCRIPTION/SEDIMENTOLOGY
CORE DESCRIPTION REQUIRES A VARIETY OF EXPERTISE DEPENDING ON THE EXPEDITION OBJECTIVES AND MATERIAL TO BE RECOVERED. SCIENTISTS ARE TYPICALLY INVITED TO SAIL AS
SEDIMENTOLOGISTS, PETROLOGISTS OR IGNEOUS PETROLOGISTS, ALTERATION PETROLOGISTS, STRUCTURAL GEOLOGISTS, VOLCANOLOGISTS, ETC.
